        <h1>WELCOME TO e-EXAMINATION</h1>
       
            <p>Rule:</p>
            <p>1. Eligibility: The e-exam portal could display the eligibility criteria for taking the exam. This could include age, educational qualifications, and other requirements.

               <br> 2. Test duration: The portal could specify the duration of the test and the time allotted for each section.
                
               <br>  3. Exam format: The exam format could be explained, including the number of questions, the type of questions, and the marking scheme.
                
               <br> 4. Rules for taking the exam: The portal could display the rules for taking the exam, including guidelines for logging in, using the navigation tools, and submitting answers.
                
               <br> 5. Prohibited items: The portal could specify the items that are prohibited during the exam, including electronic devices, notes, and books.
                
               <br> 6. Conduct guidelines: The portal could display guidelines for behavior during the exam, including guidelines for communicating with other test-takers and guidelines for using the chat function.
                
               <br> 7. Consequences of misconduct: The portal could outline the consequences of misconduct during the exam, including disqualification from the exam and possible legal action.
                
               <br> 8. Privacy policy: The portal could display its privacy policy, including how personal information will be used and how it will be protected.
                
               <br> 9. Technical requirements: The portal could specify the technical requirements for taking the exam, including internet speed, supported browsers, and device requirements.
                
               <br> 10. Support resources: The portal could provide information on support resources available to test-takers, such as technical support and contact information for the exam administrator.
            </p>
        
        
